sample.title: Guantanamo detainee paid compensation by UK to settle torture complicity case | BBC News
sample.description:

Abu Zubaydah was the first man subjected to the CIA's "enhanced interrogation‚Äù techniques after the 11 September 2001 attacks. It was claimed he was a senior al-Qaeda member. The US government later withdrew the allegation.
 
MI5 and MI6 passed questions to the CIA for use during Zubaydah's interrogations despite knowing of his extreme mistreatment.
 
He brought a legal claim against the UK on the basis that its intelligence services were "complicit" in his torture.
